<subSubSection lastPageId="47" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,1589,1935]" box="[198,824,1709,1735]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,549,1709,1735]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis. Imago (external).</emphasis>
Wingspan: 
<quantity box="[690,820,1709,1735]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="12.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="12.0">12–13 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,1589,1935]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Head, patagia, anterior part of tegulae, prothorax, basal part of costa, triangular patch of medial area, major part of subterminal, and terminal area, including fringes: black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,1589,1935]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Forewing ground colour: beige suffused with light-brown scales, subterminal area with beige-brown patches.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,1589,1935]" box="[197,848,1909,1935]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Abdomen: dark grey, with dorsal tuft on basal segment.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[197,755,152,178]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Reniform stigma: small, yellow, black outlined.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Hindwing: beige; with narrow brown terminal line and indistinct discal spot; fringes white basally, otherwise beige.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[197,770,272,298]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Underside: forewing grey brown, hindwing grey.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[198,1374,311,338]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,384,311,337]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Tegumen: long, medially narrow; basally and dorso-laterally broad, platelike (apo.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[197,1158,352,378]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Vinculum: two branched; centre one barlike; posterior one branchlike, not curved.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[197,581,392,418]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Saccus: short, broadly V shaped.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[197,643,432,458]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Valvae: asymmetrical; relatively long.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[197,1271,472,498]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ampulla: slightly asymmetrical, dorsal lobe twice as broad as ventral fingerlike lobe (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[197,684,512,538]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Digitus: small, triangular, apically setose.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Anellus plate: prominently asymmetrical; with short, free, curved, heavily sclerotised brushlike structure; head on one side clothed with stout setae (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[197,774,632,658]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Juxta: trapezoid, with medial cleft on dorsal side.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Phallus: coecum short and broadly triangular; broadest by ductus ejaculatorius; subapically smoothly and upwards curved 90 
<superScript attach="left" box="[374,382,712,726]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">o</superScript>
to pointed tip (apo.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[197,564,754,780]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Vesica: armed with small plate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[198,1035,794,820]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,473,794,820]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[487,610,795,820]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Fustis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biextuta">
<emphasis box="[487,610,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">F. biextuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[833,996,794,820]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Fustis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[833,904,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fustis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[198,869,834,860]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">- beige ground-colour, with contrasting wing pattern;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[198,400,874,900]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">male genitalia, in</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[198,883,914,940]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">- tegumen basally and dorsally with platelike features;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[198,1006,954,980]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">- shape of ampulla, dorsal part broad, and ventral part fingerlike;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[198,733,994,1020]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">- smoothly curved, brushlike anellus; and</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,1100]" box="[198,698,1034,1060]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">- phallus subapically curved upwards.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
